\section*{Introdction}

First,some simple code would be given to import the tidyverse package.

\begin{enumerate}
  \item Importing data
\end{enumerate}


<<>>=
library(tidyverse)
mpg
@

\begin{enumerate}
  \item Ploting using ggplot2 package
\end{enumerate}

<<fig=TRUE,tidy=TRUE,highlight=FALSE>>=
ggplot2::ggplot(data = mpg)+geom_point(mapping=aes(x=displ,y=hwy))
@

\section*{dplyr}

This package mainly used to deal with data transformation.

This package include some useful functions,including \emph{filter(),pick observations by their values},\emph{arrange(),reorder the rows},\emph{select(),pick variables by their names,mutate(),create new variables with functions of existing variables}.

Next,I will introduce them one by one.

<<>>=
library(nycflights13)
library(tidyverse)
filter(flights,month==1,day==1)
filter(flights,month%in%c(11,12))
@




